data.title: Google's stock rally hits 63% in 4 months with shares at $286, analyst say far from over. Price targets raised to $330 and $335 by Goldman Sachs and Bank of America.
data.description: Alphabet Inc. (NASDAQ: GOOGL) has experienced a significant surge in its stock price, rising nearly 5% to $286 and marking a 63% rally over the last four months, its strongest performance since its 2004 IPO. This increase follows a strong third-quarter report, with analysts at Goldman Sachs and Bank of America raising their price targets for the company. Goldman Sachs raised its 12-month price target to $330, a 15% upside from current levels, citing Alphabet's strong position in AI-powered consumer and enterprise computing. Bank of America raised its price target to $335, implying a 17% upside. Analysts believe Alphabet's AI momentum is accelerating and that there is still room for growth in the stock price.

data.title: Roblox reports $1.92B in quarterly bookings, 151.5M DAUs with 70% growth, revenue at $1.36B & 39.6B hours engaged.
data.description: Roblox Corp. (NYSE: RBLX) shares declined following the release of its fiscal third-quarter results. The company achieved a remarkable 70% year-on-year growth in quarterly bookings, reaching $1.92 billion, surpassing the analyst consensus of $1.65 billion. Despite this success, the video game developer reported an EPS loss of 37 cents, performing better than the expected 48-cent loss. Revenue for the American video game developer increased by 48% year-on-year to $1.36 billion. User engagement metrics showed significant growth with Average Daily Active Users (DAUs) reaching 151.5 million, a 70% increase year-on-year. Hours Engaged rose by 91% year-on-year to 39.6 billion. The average monthly unique payers totaled 35.8 million.

data.title: Roblox Corp reported Q3 2025 earnings call: DAUs 151.5M, revenue $1.36B, bookings $1.92B, monthly payers 35.8M, $427.9M DevEx.
data.description: Roblox Corp (NYSE: RBLX) reported its third-quarter financial results before the market open, with the CEO David Baszucki discussing the progress made in capturing 3.2% of the global gaming content market. The company saw growth in daily active users (DAUs), hitting 151.5 million, up 70% year on year. Revenue for Q3 was $1.36 billion, up 48% year on year, and bookings were $1.92 billion, up 70% year on year. The company highlighted ongoing investments in technology, safety, and AI, emphasizing a commitment to innovation and long-term growth. Important numbers include DAUs up 70%, revenue at $1.36 billion, bookings at $1.92 billion, and monthly unique payers at 35.8 million, up 88% year on year.

data.title: Starbucks reports mixed Q4 results; analysts optimistic. Buy ratings with price targets of $84 and $105. Positive sales growth.
data.description: Starbucks Corp (NASDAQ: SBUX) released its fiscal Q4 results, receiving mixed feedback from analysts. TD Cowen's Andrew Charles kept a Buy rating and a $84 price target, while BTIG's Peter Saleh reiterated a Buy rating with a $105 price target. TD Cowen noted that Starbucks' North America same-store sales turned positive in September and further improved in October. The company's protein beverage platform, launched on Sept. 29, has seen growing awareness. Additionally, Starbucks closed 435 stores as part of their strategy. For more details, visit Benzinga.com.

data.title: CoreWeave (Nasdaq: CRWV) acquires Marimo Inc., creator of marimo notebook, a Python AI-developer tool.
data.description: In Livingston, New Jersey, and Redwood City, California, CoreWeave, Inc. (Nasdaq: CRWV) revealed today its plan to purchase Marimo Inc., the company behind the open-source marimo notebook. This notebook is designed for Python and tailored for AI and data tasks, offering a reactive development environment. CoreWeave focuses on enabling AI advancement, serving as a critical player in shaping the future of AI technology. Positioned as the premier cloud platform specifically designed for AI purposes, CoreWeave is at the forefront of driving AI innovation.

data.title: CoreWeave (Nasdaq: CRWV) did not receive stockholder approval for acquiring Core Scientific in an all-stock transaction.
data.description: Livingston, New Jersey - CoreWeave, Inc. (Nasdaq: CRWV), known as The Essential Cloud for AI™, addressed the results of Core Scientific’s recent Special Meeting of Stockholders. The meeting was held to vote on the adoption of the Agreement and Plan of Merger for CoreWeave to acquire Core Scientific through an all-stock deal. Initial figures indicate that the proposal did not secure the required approval from Core Scientific's stockholders, leading to the agreement not being finalized.

data.title: SpaceX shifts $894M in Bitcoin holdings; Musk's company's moves prompt speculation on its intentions with the cryptocurrency.
data.description: SpaceX, the company founded and led by Elon Musk, has not explicitly confirmed whether it is selling its Bitcoin holdings or reevaluating its security measures. Despite the lack of official statement, the aerospace manufacturer and space transportation company is actively engaging with the cryptocurrency, signaling ongoing interest. The ambiguity surrounding SpaceX's actions has led to speculation and interest from observers in the crypto community. It remains uncertain if the company is making significant changes to its approach toward Bitcoin or simply enhancing its security protocols.

data.title: Osteopathic medical profession reaches 200,000 physicians and students for the first time, showcasing significant growth.
data.description: On October 30, 2025, in Chicago, the American Osteopathic Association (AOA) revealed a significant milestone for the osteopathic medical profession: surpassing 200,000 individuals, including physicians and medical students. data.title: Space-based laser communication market growing at 16.5% CAGR due to demand for high-speed satellite data links and reliable transmission.
data.description: The Space-based Laser Communication Market is experiencing significant growth due to the increasing demand for fast, secure, and dependable data transfer within satellite networks. This growth is propelled by the rising deployment of small satellites, a growing need for broadband connectivity, and a transition towards optical technology. These factors have led to a surge in market demand, with global revenues expected to reach substantial figures in the near future.
